Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liverpool}}\n[[Category:Geography of Liverpool|Climate]]\n[[Category:Climate of England]]\n[[Category:Climate by city]]\n", "text_old": "{{climate chart\n| [[Liverpool, United Kingdom]]\n|2.4|7.2|74.9\n|2.1|7.3|54.4\n|3.8|9.4|63.6\n|5.1|12.2|54.3\n|7.9|15.6|54.9\n|11.1|17.9|66.2\n|13.3|19.7|59.0\n|13.2|19.4|68.9\n|11.0|17.3|71.7\n|8.2|13.9|97.3\n|5.2|10.2|82.6\n|2.5|7.5|88.8\n|float=right\n|clear=none\n}}\n\n[[File:Liverpool_Snow_Jan_05_2010_(28).jpg|alt=|align=right|thumb|Snow falling in [[Liverpool city centre]] during the [[Winter of 2010\u201311 in Great Britain and Ireland|winter of 2010]]]]\n\nThe '''climate of [[Liverpool]]''' features a [[Temperate climate|temperate]] [[maritime climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]]: ''Cfb''), with relatively mild summers, cool winters and rainfall spread fairly evenly throughout the year. Since 1867, rainfall and temperature records for the city have been kept at [[Bidston]] Observatory, as well as atmospheric pressure records since 1845. However, the site closed down in 2002, and a weather station in [[Crosby, Merseyside|Crosby]] has been used by the [[Met Office]] since.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pol.ac.uk/appl/hist_met/|title=Historical weather data for Bidston Observatory|publisher=Web.archive.org|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110224035445/http://www.pol.ac.uk/appl/hist_met/|archivedate=24 February 2011|url-status=|accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref> There have also been other stations to operate in the Liverpool area, including: [[Wallasey]] (1924\u20131993), [[West Kirby]] (1926\u20131993), [[Aigburth]] (1968\u20131993), and [[Liverpool John Lennon Airport]] (1950\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_b28b9015-7131-45e0-8199-252019280581/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1924 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_98924d71-162c-47de-92ec-962510c36157/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1926 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_91ed7d2e-fb65-45d8-8a83-0cdc1dcd4f14/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1968 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_a71d6634-8acc-4700-80c7-d7eccaf162eb/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1950 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSince records began, the lowest temperature ever recorded in Liverpool is {{Convert|-17.6|C|F|abbr=}} on 21 December 2010, and the highest temperature recorded is {{Convert|34.5|C|F|abbr=}} on 2 August 1990. Although, during the [[2006 European heat wave|2006 heat wave]], a temperature of {{Convert|35.0|C|F|abbr=}} was supposedly recorded at [[Liverpool John Lennon Airport]] on 19 July 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.tutiempo.net/climate/2006/ws-33233.html|title=Climate Liverpool Airport (Year 2006) - Climate data (33233)|work=Tutiempo.net|accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref> The highest daily minimum temperature is {{Convert|20.0|C|F|abbr=}} reported on 4 occasions: 13 July 1926,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_98924d71-162c-47de-92ec-962510c36157/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1926 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> 29 July 1948,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digital.nmla.metoffice.gov.uk/IO_7aa3bf68-127c-4331-96c0-3ec97b082120/|title=The Monthly Weather Report 1948 |publisher=Met Office|accessdate=26 March 2020}}.</ref> 1 August 1995,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.tutiempo.net/climate/08-1995/ws-33233.html|title=Liverpool Airport August 1995|work=Tutiempo.net|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> and 6 August 2003<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.tutiempo.net/climate/08-2003/ws-33233.html||title=Liverpool Airport August 2003|work=Tutiempo.net|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> and the lowest daily maximum temperature is {{Convert|-9.9|C|F|abbr=}} on 20 December 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.tutiempo.net/climate/12-2010/ws-33160.html||title=Crosby December 2010|work=Tutiempo.net|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> On average, the amount of air frost days per year is below the national average, and in winter, snow is fairly common, but heavy snow is rare.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/public/weather/climate/gctb66ydw|title=Crosby climate information|date=1 May 2014|publisher=Met Office|accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref> Rain is also a common occurrence in the city, but [[Drought|droughts]] can become a problem in the summer, most recently in the [[2018 European heat wave|2018 heat wave]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-lancashire-44886776|title=Hot weather closes 55 miles of canal|last=|first=|date=20 July 2018|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=18 August 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n== Classifications ==\n{{Schemebox\n|city =Liverpool\n\n| source_k =<ref>{{cite web |title=Liverpool, England K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification |url=https://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=332330&cityname=Liverpool,+England,+United+Kingdom |website=Weatherbase |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n| initial_k ={{D-P|''Cfb''}} \n| description_k =[[Oceanic climate]]{{Efn|Also called marine west coast.|name=|group=}}\n\n| source_t =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kkh.ltrr.arizona.edu/kkh/climate/trewartha_maps.htm|title=Trewartha maps|website=kkh.ltrr.arizona.edu|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n| initial_t ={{Forest|''Do''}} \n| description_t =Temperate [[oceanic climate]]\n\n| source_a =<ref>{{Citation|last=Cmapm|first=Kliimav\u00f6\u00f6tmed svg: Urmasderivative work|title=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439: \u041a\u043b\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0441\u0430 \u0417\u0435\u043c\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0411. \u041f. \u0410\u043b\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0443.|date=2011-06-16|url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Alisov%27s_classification_of_climate_ru.jpg|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n| initial_a ={{n/a}} \n| description_a =[[Temperate climate]]{{Efn|Mid-latitude temperate maritime climate|name=|group=}}\n\n| source_s =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://i.pinimg.com/originals/c5/16/b8/c516b8c463fa99df0da778f768c85965.jpg|title=World Strahler Climate Map|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n| initial_s = {{n/a}}\n| description_s =[[Oceanic climate|Marine west-coast]]\n\n| source_tw =<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Feddema|first=Johannes J.|date=January 2005|title=A Revised Thornthwaite-Type Global Climate Classification|journal=Physical Geography|language=en|volume=26|issue=6|pages=442\u2013466|doi=10.2747/0272-3646.26.6.442|issn=0272-3646}}</ref>\n| initial_tw =<center>''C2 B'1''</center>\n| description_tw =Moist subhumid\n\n| source_n =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spektrum.de/lexikon/geographie/klimaklassifikation/4159|title=Klimaklassifikation|website=www.spektrum.de|language=de|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n| initial_n ={{n/a}} \n| description_n =West side/maritime climate\n}}\n\n== Temperature ==\nThe average yearly high temperature in Liverpool is {{Convert|13.2|C|F|abbr=}} and the average yearly low temperature is {{Convert|7.2|C|F|abbr=}}. The average daily mean is {{Convert|10.1|C|F|abbr=}}.\n\n=== Averages ===\n\n{{Weather box\n|location=[[Crosby, Merseyside|Crosby]],{{efn|Weather station is located {{convert|7|mi|0|abbr=out}} from the Liverpool city centre.}} elevation: {{convert|30|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}, 1981\u20132010 averages\n|collapsed=\n|metric first=y\n|single line=y\n|Jan high C=7.2\n|Feb high C=7.3\n|Mar high C=9.4\n|Apr high C=12.2\n|May high C=15.6\n|Jun high C=17.9\n|Jul high C=19.7\n|Aug high C=19.4\n|Sep high C=17.3\n|Oct high C=13.9\n|Nov high C=10.2\n|Dec high C=7.5\n|year high C=13.2\n|Jan mean C=4.8\n|Feb mean C=4.7\n|Mar mean C=6.6\n|Apr mean C=8.7\n|May mean C=11.8\n|Jun mean C=14.5\n|Jul mean C=16.5\n|Aug mean C=16.3\n|Sep mean C=14.2\n|Oct mean C=11.1\n|Nov mean C=7.7\n|Dec mean C=5.0\n|year mean C=10.1\n|Jan low C=2.4\n|Feb low C=2.1\n|Mar low C=3.8\n|Apr low C=5.1\n|May low C=7.9\n|Jun low C=11.1\n|Jul low C=13.3\n|Aug low C=13.2\n|Sep low C=11.0\n|Oct low C=8.2\n|Nov low C=5.2\n|Dec low C=2.5\n|year low C=7.2\n|source 1=[[Met Office]]<ref name=\"Met Averages\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/public/weather/climate/gctb66ydw|title=Crosby 1981\u20132010 Averages|accessdate=9 April 2019|publisher=Met Office}}</ref>|source 2=[[National Oceanography Centre]]<ref name=\"NOC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.pol.ac.uk/appl/hist_met/|title=Historical weather data for Bidston Observatory |accessdate=19 August 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110224035445/http://www.pol.ac.uk/appl/hist_met/|archivedate= 24 February 2011|publisher=NOC}}</ref>}}\n\n=== Extremes ===\nDue to Liverpool having an oceanic climate, extremes of temperatures are rare.<ref name=\"worldatlas1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/what-are-the-characteristics-of-an-oceanic-type-of-climate.html|title=What Are The Characteristics Of An Oceanic Type Of Climate?|date=5 February 2018|website=World Atlas|accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Weather box\n|location=Crosby, elevation: {{convert|30|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}, 1867\u2013present extremes{{efn|From 1867\u20132002, extremes were recorded at the Bidston Observatory in Wirral. Since 2002, extremes were recorded at Crosby, Sefton.}}\n|collapsed=\n|metric first=y\n|single line=y\n|Jan record high C=15.1\n|Feb record high C=18.9\n|Mar record high C=21.2\n|Apr record high C=25.3\n|May record high C=28.2\n|Jun record high C=30.7\n|Jul record high C=34.3\n|Aug record high C=34.5\n|Sep record high C=30.4\n|Oct record high C=25.9\n|Nov record high C=18.7\n|Dec record high C=15.8\n|Jan record low C=-12.8\n|Feb record low C=-11.3\n|Mar record low C=-7.5\n|Apr record low C=-5.0\n|May record low C=-1.7\n|Jun record low C=2.